David Imoh, the sound engineer burnt to death by a mob in Lagos State has been laid to rest. Recall that mob suspected to be commercial motorcyclists near Beer Barn, a leisure facility in the Lekki axis of Lagos on the 12th of May, 2022 attacked and set Imoh on fire. Imoh was attacked by a commercial motorcyclist, popularly known as Okada rider after having a misunderstanding over N100. -Advertisement- The state police command had subsequently arrested five suspects over the lynching of the sound engineer. According to a family member, a ceremony of songs was held for the deceased on Thursday, June 2 at the Church of God Mission Intl, Victoria Island Zonal Headquarters, Garden City of God, T. F. Kuboye Street, Oniru, Lagos. POLL